Description: Cisco Enterprise SIP firmware support for Asterisk chan_pjsip
 Ten shared modules that add Cisco Enterprise SIP firmware
 (7975 / 8841 / 8861 / 8865 …) compatibility to Asterisk's chan_pjsip
 channel driver, without patching Asterisk core.
 .
 Provides BLF Speed Dial line-button support, the Cisco RemoteCC
 optionsind/bulkupdate REGISTER flow the firmware expects, server-pushed
 unsolicited Event: presence NOTIFYs, Cisco-flavoured PIDF body generation
 (with presence-state-driven BLF lamps for DND), DND / CFwdALL / HuntGroup
 softkey handling plus matching CLIs and CISCO_*() dialplan functions,
 CLI service-control NOTIFYs (check-sync / restart / reset / prt-report),
 and Cisco call signaling headers / SDP quirks.
 .
 Handles Cisco RemoteCC REFER traffic including HLog, MCID, Park,
 ParkMonitor, and Record (StartRecording / StopRecording via MixMonitor)
 softkeys. Conference control: a Confrn-built multimix bridge with
 phone-side UI promotion (Conference glyph + un-hold), the Join /
 Select / Unselect multi-call merge, RmLastConf, and the ConfList
 participant list with its Mute / Remove / Update action softkeys.
 .
 NAT-friendly: a global on_tx_request hook rewrites the Request-URI and
 To-URI back to the phone's self-advertised host:port when Asterisk's
 rewrite_contact=yes has left an x-ast-orig-host parameter on the
 Contact-derived RURI, so unsolicited NOTIFYs and REFERs reach Cisco
 phones behind NAT instead of being rejected with 400 Bad Request.
 .
 Targets phones running Cisco's Enterprise SIP firmware which would
 otherwise need either CallManager or the cisco-usecallmanager chan_sip
 patch. This package supersedes that patch for sites running chan_pjsip.
